lg.l:
Five
                                                  windows light the cavern'd Man; thro' one he
                                                  breathes the air;

And see
                                                  small portions of the eternal world that ever
                                                  groweth;

Thro'
                                                  one, himself pass out what time he please, but he
                                                  will not;

Into my
                                                  parlour and sat down, and took my pen to
                                                  write;

And we
                                                  will crown thy head with garlands of the ruddy
                                                  vine;

Bring
                                                  Palamabron horned priest, skipping upon the
                                                  mountains;

One
                                                  hour they lay buried beneath the ruins of that
                                                  hall;

Shut up
                                                  in finite revolutions, and man became an
                                                  Angel;

Above
                                                  the rest the howl was heard from Westminster
                                                  louder & louder;

On
                                                  golden chariots raging, with red wheels dropping
                                                  with blood;

The
                                                  Tigers couch upon the prey & suck the ruddy
                                                  tide;
